5-Design-for-Game-Center":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Get your game’s interface ready for Game Center. We’ll show you how to deliver personalized touches to the GameKit interface that provide a rich experience for players, with features like achievements, leaderboards, and multiplayer gaming. Learn how to customize your game’s access point, design collectible card-style achievements and multiple leaderboards, and adapt your interface for all platforms and orientations."}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Design for Game Center","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10145-design-for-game-center","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10145-Design-for-Game-Center"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10619-Tap-into-Game-Center-Leaderboards-Achievements-and-Multiplayer":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Level up your Game Center integration and enable players to compare scores on leaderboards, earn valuable achievements, and engage with other players. Organize special events like weekly championships, daily showdowns, or 1-hour competitions using recurring leaderboards. Create up to 100 unique achievements for your game. And we’ll show you how to set up real-time or turn-based multiplayer matches for your Game Center players."}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Tap into Game Center: Leaderboards, Achievements, and Multiplayer","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10619-tap-into-game-center-leaderboards-achievements-and-multiplayer","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10619-Tap-into-Game-Center-Leaderboards-Achievements-and-Multiplayer"},"WWDC20.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC20.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC22-10064-Reach-new-players-with-Game-Center-dashboard":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text